This is an executive summary of the policies, procedures and activities for compliance with the EPA's Accidental Release Prevention Requirements - Risk Management Program pursuant to Title 40 Part 68 of the Code of Federal Regulations (40 CFR 68) for the KC Midstream, LLC, (KC Midstream) Irishtown facility (also known as the Swamp Angel facility). KC Midstream is a wholly-owned subsidiary of Catalyst Energy, Inc. (Catalyst Energy).



<> The accidental release prevention and emergency response policies at the stationary source [40 CFR 68.155(a)]:

The accidental release prevention and emergency response policies are addressed in the Risk Management Program & Process Safety Management Program Manual, which details the RMP program requirements as well as how KC Midstream complies with the applicable requirements.  The Irishtown facility is a non-responding facility for releases of the RMP-listed chemicals, so the site utilizes an Emergency Action Plan.  



<> The stationary source and regulated substances handled [40 CFR 68.155(b)]:

The Irishtown facility is located in Lewis Run, McKean County, Pennsylvania.  The facility compresses and processes natural gas to produce pipeline quality natural gas and NGLs.  The natural gas and NGL mixture is comprised of a flammable mixture containing the following regulated substances:



     Butane [106-97-8];

     Ethane [74-84-0];

     Isobutane [Propane, 2-methyl] [75-28-5];

     Isopentane [Butane, 2-methyl-] [78-78-4];

     Methane [74-82-8];

     Pentane [109-66-0]; and 

     Propane [74-98-6].  



<> The general accidental release prevention program and chemical-specific prevention steps [40 CFR 68.155(c)]:

The Irishtown facility is required to implement the Program Level 3 prevention program requirements under the RMP regulations. As such, the Irishtown facility will comply with the requirements for preventing or minimizing the consequences of catastrophic releases of flammable or explosive chemicals codified under 40 CFR Part 68.65
